# Search & Exploration Precedence (Token-Minimizing)

Use this order to minimize token usage and file reads. Skip ahead only when earlier steps are inapplicable.

## 1) Location already known → Read directly

If you already have an exact file path (stack trace, test failure, explicit reference), go straight to `Read` on that file and proceed with precise edits.

Do **not** do broad searches in this case.

## 2) Semantic exploration (\"how does X work\", \"where is Y\") → Serena MCP

When you need LSP-accurate navigation, blast radius, or file structure, use the **Serena** MCP server (`serena` in `.cursor/mcp.json`). It is a **shared HTTP** server (`http://127.0.0.1:24601/mcp`, systemd unit `serena-tentura.service`) — do **not** spawn stdio Serena; every new agent/client must connect to that URL. Read each tool's schema from the MCP descriptors before calling.

- **`get_symbols_overview`** — top-level symbols in a file (prefer over reading whole files)
- **`find_symbol`** — locate a class/function/variable by name
- **`find_declaration`** — go to definition
- **`find_referencing_symbols`** — who references a symbol (impact / blast radius)
- **`find_implementations`** — implementations of an interface/abstract symbol
- **`search_for_pattern`** — regex search across the project
- **`find_file`** — locate files by name/path fragment

Project `tentura` is already active on the shared server. Only call **`activate_project`** if Serena reports no active project.

Use `Read` only for the specific file(s) and line ranges you are about to modify.

## 3) Grep/Glob fallback only

Use `Grep`/`Glob` **only** when:
- Serena MCP is unavailable or the language server is not ready, or
- you have an exact string/symbol and need a precise match quickly.

## Generated Dart files — avoid reading/editing

Never read or edit generated files; use the source instead:

- `**.g.dart`
- `**.freezed.dart`
- `**.gr.dart`
- `**.config.dart`
- `**.schema.dart`
